page.title: 10Wildlife
page.content: Along the hedgerows & fields there is much wild life to be observed. Rabbits, Hare & Fox lie side by side & survive the farmers activities very well. Plenty of common birds such as Sparrow, Thrush, Blackbird, Yellow Hammers, Wagtails & Wren are all prevelent in this part of the country. Noticeable are an abundance of Gulls which live inland all the year round & speckle the fields with white patches on newly ploughed ground. Pheasant, Partridge, Pigeon & Magpies seem more apparent each year in the trees. Due to Dutch Elm disease, trees are disapearing quite frequently, & it is hoped many more will be planted in the future to house the wild life. In woodland there are many interesting features not commonly observed during daylight hours. There are badgers present, with sets clearly visible.
